Well, 1303-1 isn't just anechoic, and 1302-1 isn't just pitch-dark. In both cases, the sense that wasn't suppressed gets subjected to hallucinations that may or may not be part of the anomalous effect. (The ambiguity of that is something I like quite a lot, personally.) Also which chamber is anechoic or pitch-dark at any given time, if any, keeps changing. That's definitely quite anomalous







